  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Stealth components minimize a ships visibility, allowin=
g it
  to evade detection &#8211; particularly at long range.<o:p></o:p></span><=
/p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Note that stealth components do NOT make a ship complet=
ely invisible.
  They simply reduce its detectability by enemy sensors.<o:p></o:p></span><=
/p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Each stealth component has a rating specifying its leve=
l of
  stealth cloaking. This rating is matched to the size of the ship that uses
  the component. The distance that the ship becomes visible to enemy sensors
  can then be calculated.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>When a stealth component rating exactly equals the size=
 of
  the ship then the ship&#8217;s actual stealth cloaking is 50%. This means
  that the ship will become visible to enemy sensors at 50% of the range th=
at
  an uncloaked ship is visible.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>When the stealth component rating is higher than the sh=
ip
  size then the ship&#8217;s actual stealth cloaking improves. For example =
if
  the stealth component has a rating of 500 and the ship size is 250 then t=
he
  ship&#8217;s actual stealth cloaking is 25% (it becomes visible to enemy
  sensors at 25% of the normal range).<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>The formula for calculating a ship&#8217;s actual steal=
th
  cloaking is as follows:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.5in'><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font=
-style:
  normal'><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;mso-no-proof:=
yes'>Visibility
  Range =3D (stealth rating / ship size) x 50%<o:p></o:p></span></i></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Only one stealth component is required to provide benef=
its
  &#8211; additional components do not provide cumulative effects</span>.</=
p>
